		"project_id": "2366392184",
		"section_id": "213871607",
		"parent_id": null,
		"order": 1,
		"content": "🤖 AI Model Selection Guide",
		"description": "**Purpose:** Guidelines for choosing the right AI model for different tasks to optimize cost and performance.\n\n---\n\n## Available Models\n\n| Model | Alias | Strengths | Cost |\n|-------|-------|-----------|------|\n| **Claude Opus 4** | `opus` | Complex reasoning, architecture, planning | $$$ |\n| **Claude Sonnet 4** | `sonnet` | Balanced capability/cost, general tasks | $$ |\n| **Gemini Pro** | (default) | Good all-rounder, fast | $ |\n| **Gemini Flash** | — | Quick lookups, simple tasks | ¢ |\n\n---\n\n## When to Use Each\n\n### 🧠 Opus (High-Capability Tasks)\n- Architecture and system design\n- Complex multi-step planning\n- Nuanced conversations with humans\n- Writing documentation/runbooks\n- Debugging complex issues\n- PDR/RFC creation\n\n### ⚡ Sonnet (General Tasks)\n- Standard task execution\n- Code generation/review\n- When Opus usage >75%\n- Most day-to-day work\n\n### 🚀 Gemini Pro (Default)\n- Routine operations\n- Heartbeat checks\n- Simple queries\n- Background monitoring\n\n### 💨 Gemini Flash (Quick Tasks)\n- Simple lookups\n- Status checks\n- Formatting/parsing\n\n---\n\n## Sub-Agent Delegation\n\n**Spawn sub-agents for:**\n- Documentation generation\n- Web research compilation\n- Bulk operations (copying tasks, etc.)\n- Runbook creation\n- Any parallelizable grunt work\n\n**Keep on main agent:**\n- Direct human conversation\n- Decisions requiring context\n- Security-sensitive operations\n\n---\n\n## Usage Thresholds\n\n| Usage Level | Action |\n|-------------|--------|\n| 0-50% | Stay on Opus freely |\n| 50-75% | Use Opus for complex, Sonnet for routine |\n| 75%+ | Switch to Sonnet, reserve Opus for critical |\n| 90%+ | Gemini only, alert human |\n\n---\n\n## Command Examples\n\n```bash\n# Check current usage\n/status\n\n# Override model for session\nsession_status with model parameter\n\n# Spawn sub-agent (uses default model)\nsessions_spawn with task\n```\n\n---\n\n**Remember:** Expensive models for expensive problems. Don't use a sledgehammer to hang a picture frame.\n\n---\n\n*Last updated: 2026-01-29*",
